12/10/2003
BERNE, Switzerland -- Bulgaria and Greece are set to play in the 2004 European Cup finals in Portugal after the last round of qualification games on Saturday (11 October). In its last game, Bulgaria lost to Croatia in Zagreb 0-1, while Greece beat Northern Ireland 1-0. The Croatians still have a chance to qualify, as they placed second in their group and made it to the playoff round. Turkey will also appear in the playoffs after it drew its game with England 0-0 in Istanbul. Serbia-Montenegro beat Wales in Cardiff 3-2, but this was not enough to take the team to the playoff stage. Bosnia and Herzegovina drew its game with Denmark 1-1 and failed to qualify for the finals. (AP, AFP, Reuters - 11/10/03)
